---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
  description:
    "Organizers - UR-RAD 2025 AAAI Fall Symposium on Unifying Representations for Robot Application Development",
  title: "Organizers",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
  <h1 class="title mb-6">Organizers</h1>
  <div class="prose prose-citrus max-w-none px-4">
    <p class="text-lg mb-8">
      The UR-RAD 2025 symposium is organized by researchers dedicated to
      advancing robot application development and unifying representations in
      robotics.
    </p>

    <h2>Organizing Committee</h2>
    <div
      class="grid gap-4 sm:gap-6 grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 mb-8"
    >
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Ruchen Wen</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">Colgate University</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-1">David Porfirio</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">
          Naval Research Laboratory
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Saad Elbeleidy</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">Peerbots</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Laura M. Hiatt</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">
          Naval Research Laboratory
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Ross Mead</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">Semio</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Andrew Schoen</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">Semio</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Willie Wilson</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">
          Franklin & Marshall College
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-1">Laura Stegner</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">
          George Washington University
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Previous Organizing Committees</h2>
    <p class="mb-6">
      UR-RAD has been successfully organized by dedicated teams of researchers
      who share a vision for advancing robot application development.
    </p>

    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:gap-6 grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-3">UR-RAD 2024</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">
          Organized as part of the AAAI Fall Symposium series at Westin
          Arlington Gateway, Arlington, VA, USA
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 border border-special-lighter rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-3">UR-RAD 2023</h3>
        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">
          The inaugural symposium held at Westin Arlington Gateway, Arlington,
          VA, USA
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Steering Committee</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The UR-RAD symposium series is guided by a steering committee of experts
      in robotics, AI, and related fields who provide strategic direction and
      ensure continuity across symposium editions.
    </p>

    <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 bg-special-lighter rounded-lg mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Prior Events</h3>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-2">
        This is the 3rd iteration of UR-RAD at the AAAI Fall Symposium Series.
        Prior iterations of UR-RAD can be found below:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-xs sm:text-sm">
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://sites.google.com/view/aaai-ur-rad-24-symposium"
            class="citrus-link">UR-RAD 2024</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://sites.google.com/view/aaai-ur-rad-23-symposium"
            class="citrus-link">UR-RAD 2023</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Get Involved</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Interested in contributing to the organization of future UR-RAD
      symposiums? We welcome volunteers and collaborators who share our vision
      for advancing robot application development.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 p-3 sm:p-4 bg-accent-base/5 rounded-lg">
      <p class="text-center">
        <strong>Contact the Organizing Committee</strong><br />
        For questions about organization, collaboration opportunities, or general
        inquiries:<br />
        <a href="mailto:urrad.symposium@gmail.com" class="citrus-link"
          >urrad.symposium@gmail.com</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
